insta_description:
I'm lucky to spend the next month and a half making collections of the stunning genus, Calochortus (Liliaceae), taking social distancing to the most lovely and mountainous extreme that someone like John Muir would have been proud of. My lab at @uwbotany in collaboration with a lab at @cornelluniversity are working on a grant from the @nsfgov to study the evolution of this wonderful genus. I'll start by making collections of 4 target species all thought to be most closely related, yet show striking morphological differences in floral form, 2 are 'cat's ears' as seen here, and two are 'fairly lanterns' that never fully open. By studying my collections we are hoping to work out which form evolved first and which genes are turned on and off during bud development to produce the two forms. Later I will be collecting many more of the ~70 species to build a phylogenetic tree for the genus which we will use to map historical patterns of biogeography and trait evolution onto the group. 
Pictured here are C. monophyllus (VU) in yellow, C. tolmiei in white, and some snow that the Sierra Mountains just got this weekend after the driest February in history.
.
.
.

insta_description: Looking for a place to be socially distant? About a month ago we visited Death Valley and absolutely loved it. Holding numerous records (flattest, lowest, hottest, etc.), spring is one of the best times to visit the park. Geographically, hiking through Badwater Basin was such a unique experience - the white on the ground isn‚Äôt sand, but salt. The crystals are remarkably hard, and the whole world sparkles under the sun. The experience is like hiking on the surface of a giant quartz crystal. The hike to cross the basin is about six miles one way, but you need only head out about three miles to completely lose sight of people. insta_description:
Waning Crescent Moon.
GROUNDING, with my prayerüïØCreating a connection with you, woven in words as love letters is my humble grounding prayer today. üïØPrayers for you & your loved ones.

Hello my love, how are you?
May I please offer this space for you to check in?
I would absolutely love to hear how you‚Äôre holding up. Got any  coping tips? Need some coping tips? Please feel free to comment here. üïØPrayers for calm & kind space.

On this Wednesday ruled by Mercury the planet of communication, element of air, I am happy to share with you a few spoonfuls of lovin‚Äô.
My little family & big family are all physically well so far. Here in Southern California we are preparing for high winds this afternoon & a rainstorm tomorrow (Thursday). üïØPrayers for houseless folx.

It has been a rollercoaster of rapid adjustment for my 2 teenagers.  Visual communications in youth social media has been less smooth than I dreamed. There is a huge variety of factors that swirl through the air where we live and not all of the teenagers in their life have been able or willing to isolate.
It‚Äôs made it a whole lot more pressure in the already super charged atmosphere of being in a teenage body. üïØPrayers for teenagers.

My sweetheart is working triple overtime as their work is servicing medical equipment & in my lifelong home in Orange County it is all hands on deck supporting hospitals. üïØPrayers for all folks in the MEDICAL FEILD.

Many of you have checked on Mama & Pops (85 & 81).Thank you for that! They are cozy & well just 2 miles from me. They live in a 55+ condo complex in a part of town with predominantly elderly folks. The collective field of memory keepers there is so special & important. üïØPrayers for elders.

We are creating a framework based on pleasure as best we can, in our isolation. Today that means sanitizing our home by cycling through a mountain of laundry and finishing my VLOG for my YouTube channel. üïØPrayers for Witches. 
Sending you Love&Magick,
Angela x.

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
On Monday, a mandate came out for 6 #bayarea counties to implement #shelterinplace policies for their residents. That means that we must stay in our homes, practicing #socialdistancing, at all times except for a few approved activities including going to the grocery store, medical appointments, & exercise (+ a few more but you get the idea). Everything is closed except for businesses that are deemed ‚Äúessential‚Äù or who can provide delivery or takeout options.
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
I have #depression & #anxiety. There have been moments in the last few days where I have become panicked, angry, frustrated, scared, deeply sad, & at times, only able to get out of bed when coaxed by the husband. ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
I am having all of these emotions & they are valid. If you are having these feelings, you are not alone. This is a crazy, never-before-seen, changing-everyday time. Yet, I am still going to show up to work. I am still going to be an incredible #nurse for my patients & colleagues. I am going to continue to support #nurses & #futurenurses every day through my work with @newthingnurse, @enaorg, @aacn, & all the amazing online nurse groups on social media. üíØ
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
Despite everything, I am still hopeful. What makes me hopeful is knowing that there are so many incredibly passionate, smart, talented #healthcare professionals & supporters who are working together to overcome the COVID19 challenge. I see you online in photos. I speak to you everyday via messenger, phone, text, email. I work with you at the bedside. I have surrounded myself with all of you + my family & friends. Together, we will get through this. That is how I am coping. üíõüíõüíõüíõüíõüíõüíõüíõüíõ
Much love to each of you. Be safe. Protect yourself & your patients. Reach out for whatever you need. Together, we got this. üíõ @newthingnurse #coronavirus #corona #nursestrong #strongertogether #mentalhealth

insta_description:
In these testing times : Mentally, Physically, Emotionally, Economically It is very important that we all realize , The Sun Sets down only to Rise Again ‚òÄÔ∏è Yes , lives are changing for people, souls are being lost , families separated , Plans falling through the roof and everybody right now is thinking : Why and What did I do to deserve this , It‚Äôs not my Fault. .
.
.
.
.

On the other side , Innocent animals have been cramped in spaces inhospitable, devoid of food , water and hygiene. They‚Äôve died deaths that neither has a reason nor a purpose known to them and some diseased animal instead of given care and love has been slaughtered and put on a dinner plate. Moreover they aren‚Äôt domesticated and Tamed ones, they‚Äôve been smuggled across bordered , abused by their handlers , isolated from their habitats and subjected to everything inhuman. .
.
.
.
.

Nature is just showing a glimpse of how it will be if this continues !! If you are reading this , there is Hope ‚ù§Ô∏è
Both the good and frustrating thing about this : It‚Äôs not permanent. Good because it isn‚Äôt going to last long, bad because we are all being tested to levels we never were !!.
.
.
.
.

Those who are confined to your own private spaces, please don‚Äôt stress eat , it only adds to your state of mind, Listen to music , Dance like crazy , meditate if you can , Get some exercise (there are tons of videos on YouTube on how you can get some while staying indoors). There is light always at the end of the tunnel ! Hold on a little while longer , instead of spreading pandemonium Radiate your positive energy and it will all be over and we can get on with our lives !! If you‚Äôve managed to read this far :
.
.
.

Sending love to those affected and Hope to those who are devoid ! Stay Healthy !
- Raghav üî± .

‚Å£
We tried calling‚Äîmany times, with no answer üòû‚Å£
‚Å£
A few days later we finally got through to someone that could give us some information. We ended up making an appointment for a tour which included catching a bus ride up to the site. ‚Å£
‚Å£
I am so glad that we persisted. The tour was fantastic‚ú®‚Äîthe park ranger was extremely knowledgeable‚Äîsharing rich details and information that came to life as we walked through the home, room by room. ‚Å£
‚Å£
I was so intrigued by the story of Eugene‚Äôs life. Full of tragedy and darkness. His home full of symbolism. A man of passion and talent. An extremely curious life. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Please go! I absolutely recommend visiting this harder to get to site. So worth it!‚Å£

accessibility_caption: Photo by Viktorija Spendjarska Steen on March 18, 2020. Image may contain: food
insta_description:
Raw Carrot Cake with Vanilla Cashew Frosting ü•ïüç∞ Finally found time to post this super easy and delicious recipe. Make it once - it will become your favorite! üòä‚ù§Ô∏è Recipe:
1 cup walnuts 
1 cup almonds
1/2 cup sunflower seeds 
1 cup pitted dates 
1 cup dried apricots
3 grated medium size carrots 
1 tsp cinnamon 
1/2 tsp ground ginger
Juice from one orange 
For the frosting:
2 cups cashews (soaked in water overnight)
1 tsp vanilla 
1/2 cup coconut milk 
Juice of half a lemon

In a blender throw all of the ingredients and pulse until everything is well combined. Add more orange juice if needed and place the batter in a cake mold. Clean the blender and throw the ingredients for the frosting and blend until you get a smooth and creamy frosting. Place it on top of the batter and freeze it for at least 3 hours.
